<p class="hcp2">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="hcp2">Now, let’s add the mechanisms which specify 
 the causal relationships between events. &nbsp;Click 
 on the “Add Mechanism” <img src="../image79.gif"
							

							width=22
							height=22
							border="0"> &nbsp;Button 
 in the Model Toolbar and drag the arrow from the “Caught wearing wire” 
 event to “Commit murder”. &nbsp;The 
 “Mechanism Type” dialog will now pop up. &nbsp;This 
 dialog will allow you to name the mechanism and specify whether the relationship 
 between the events is causal or inhibiting. &nbsp;Since 
 being caught wearing a wire is likely to get you murdered if you work 
 for the mafia, click the box labeled “As Cause.” &nbsp;We 
 also said that this event gave Tony motive for the murder, so we can name 
 this mechanism “Motive.” &nbsp;Repeat 
 this process to create an “Opportunity” mechanism from “Boat ride” to 
 “Commit murder.”</p>
